author: stefan2
msg: On the fsfs-format7 branch:  fix a number of block read inefficiencies.
When reading data,  make sure we read everything from that block (fix
for root nodes and block read).  Keep blocks properly aligned such that
they remain aligned to the underlying device's block structure.
(svn_fs_fs__rev_get_root): trigger block read just as a normal noderev
(block_read_rep_header): skip the parser if the data is already in cache
(block_read_windows): ditto; also ensure proper read block alignment
(block_read): when reading across a block boundary, read everything
from the last block as well but don't repeat this process
